            "worstRating": "1"
          },
          "reviewBody": "I was a student of this school from 1989 to 1993. It was not at all a happy place. I only have sad and chaotic memories from here. 1. My sister was abused here. We found out after she was much older. 2. I remember a new kid who joined the school had to sit without a single piece of cloth for a whole day in front of the class. The next day he became our classmate. 3. I was tied up to a bench with a rope around my neck. It was my punishment because I had bitten an adult who was hitting me. 4. I had once been locked in a toilet. It was a common punishment there.\nThese punishments were meted out by Mrs Fonseca and Miss Dalton (the principal and her daughter).",
